Monkey and Crocodile Story!
There was a monkey always eating berries on a tree and the wife crocodile was jealous of the monkey and told her husband she wanted to eat the monkey's heart.
The husband crocodile went to the monkey and said that there's another berry treee with delicous berries across the river.
The monkey went on the husband crocodile's back and the crocodile said my wife wants your heart. 
The monkey said he let his heart by his berry tree, when he went back, the monkey climbed the tree and began laughing, saying that he won't come down. 
Moral: The moral of the story is to be brave and act wisely. 
